snippet.title: Pray for Our Mothers - Barron Trump Sings
snippet.description:
Pray for Our Mothers

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

[Verse 1]
They’re the first to rise and the last to sleep
Hearts worn down but their love runs deep
They carry burdens we’ll never see
Yet smile so strong, so quietly

[Pre-Chorus]
From every corner of this land
They raise the future with their hands
No crown, no stage, no grand parade
But they’re the reason we are made

[Chorus]
So pray for our mothers, near and far
For every lesson, every scar
For the nights they cried, and the dreams they gave
For the silent strength, so pure, so brave
Lord, hear our prayer today
We pray for our mothers on this day

[Verse 2]
Some stand tall in high heels and suits
Some wear aprons, some wear boots
But no matter where they are or live
They all know what it means to give

[Pre-Chorus]
Through chaos, joy, and growing pains
They walk with grace through joy and strain
They are the light that leads us home
No one should ever walk alone

[Chorus]
So pray for our mothers, near and far
For every lesson, every scar
For the nights they cried, and the dreams they gave
For the silent strength, so pure, so brave
Lord, hear our prayer today
We pray for our mothers on this day

[Bridge]
Let peace find them in every place
Let love surround their quiet grace
And if they stumble, if they fall
Let angels rise when mothers call

[Final Chorus]
Yeah, pray for our mothers, now and then
The ones we lost, the ones we defend
And thank You, Lord, for love so wide
We see Your heart in a mother’s eyes
We lift them up today
We pray for our mothers on this day

[Outro]
From my heart to yours, let’s bow and say
We pray for our mothers…
on this sacred day.
